<zk>
	<label multiline="true">
		ZK-6011: an invalid POST request still gets the HTTP response 200.

		Steps to reproduce:
		1. Send an AU request with no session and no desktop id, e.g.
		   curl -i -X POST http://localhost:8080/&lt;context&gt;/zkau
		2. Observe the HTTP status of the response.

		Current (buggy) result:
		- HTTP/1.1 200 OK with a "ZK-Error: 410" header and an empty body.

		To verify the fix:
		- Expected: HTTP 467 "Incomplete request" for the malformed request
		  (the same status the async-update path already uses for a missing dtid),
		  so security/monitoring tools that check the HTTP status detect it.
		- A genuine ZK client (which always carries a dtid, including a multipart
		  upload whose dtid is in the body) still receives the 200 + ZK-Error
		  session-timeout protocol, so timeout handling is intact.

		This page only serves as the deployed target; the assertion is driven by
		B104_ZK_6011Test, which fires a cookie-less POST at /zkau.
	</label>
</zk>
